Can test with:
```
time = externalFunction() return (double B)
  implemented in (classname="org.apache.sysml.udf.lib.TimeWrapper");
t = time();
print("Time: " + t);
```
(Using `className` instead of `classname` does not work.)

Thanks @deron. I would have liked to put it into `log.error()` or `log.warn()` because `log.info()` contains other useful information that I might need. Most people would probably not have either of `warn` or `error` turned. 
Here is what I've done instead - redirected it to stderr. I've updated the PR with this.

@mboehm7 - letting it stay the way it is and complicating the perf scripts is not a good option.
